text: Listening to @twoscooters talk about how harassment is important. And how we are going to help you through it.
label: not_sexism

text: "I'm bringing it up for one reason. GamerGate has brought harassment into the limelight, but rest assured, it's always there."
label: not_sexism

text: This is a problem that affects everyone, but we have seen far more harassment targeting women.
label: not_sexism

text: It is fitting that we are now seeing these strong women speaking out and trying to fix problems that others are uncertain of how to tackle.
label: not_sexism

text: Oh gosh she mentioned me and #ggautoblocker in her talk and now I am blushing and trying not to sniffle.
label: not_sexism

text: In this ongoing tragedy, we found our voices & each other. We have learned to work together, and to support & encourage these amazing women.
label: not_sexism

text: I can't even find the words to describe how much I value the work of all the people I've met during this time. How much I love all of them.
label: not_sexism

text: We talk about GamerGate a lot. But the truth is, GamerGate isn't the real battle. It's a symptom of a larger problem.
label: not_sexism

text: Online harassment is something most people have faced at some point, regardless of their views on ethics in games journalism.
label: not_sexism

text: It's a really tough problem, because it's a BIG problem. It is far reaching. It has many different forms.
label: not_sexism

text: The scope of the problem can discourage people from trying to fight it. Often this leads to thinking, "what can I do? I'm just one person."
label: not_sexism

text: You aren't just one person. There are many of us, and we all have voices. But more than that, we have resources, experience, and passion.
label: not_sexism

text: You aren't alone in this. You're never alone in this.
label: not_sexism

text: We have seen so many fantastic things happen out of this tragedy. First, we have @femfreq. Amazing advocacy. A voice that is far reaching.
label: not_sexism

text: We have @crashoverridenw, an invaluable resource that provides emotional support for targets of harassment.
